@node benchmarks
8. BENCHMARKS

  All  tests was done using (included with source) timing program.  (timing
program is based on "timing.e" included with "E" guide.)


        USING (GREAT) FASTMATH library (search somewhere in aminet)
               (1500000 computations,MC68060, all caches on)
Conversion (real to integer):FPU_in_E is   17% faster than builtin real.
Conversion (integer to real):FPU_in_E is   12% faster than builtin real.
Addition                    :FPU_in_E is   14% faster than builtin real.
Multiply                    :FPU_in_E is   14% faster than builtin real.
Sine                        :FPU_in_E is   10% faster than builtin real.
Large computation           :FPU_in_E is   18% faster than builtin real.


USING  COMMODORE "SUPERFAST" math library (search somewhere on Your install
                             system disks...)
                (500000 computations,MC68060, all caches on)
Conversion (real to integer):FPU_in_E is   30% faster than builtin real.
Conversion (integer to real):FPU_in_E is   30% faster than builtin real.
Addition                    :FPU_in_E is   15% faster than builtin real.
Multiply                    :FPU_in_E is   25% faster than builtin real.
Sine                        :FPU_in_E is 1150% faster than builtin real.
Large computation           :FPU_in_E is   22% faster than builtin real.
                                   ^^^^^
                     !! LOOK AT Sine! 1150% faster !!

@endnode

